Caren Harp, a former director of the National Juvenile Justice Prosecution Center, has been nominated to be the Administrator of the Office of Juvenile Justice and Delinquency Prevention in the Department of Justice. She has experience as a chief deputy prosecuting attorney and as the chief of the Sex Crimes Prosecution Unit in New York City. She has also worked as a managing public defender and a trial attorney. Currently, she is an associate professor at Liberty University School of Law. Harp is involved in various committees and projects related to juvenile justice. She holds a B.S. in agriculture, an M.S. in agricultural economics, and a J.D. from the University of Arkansas â€“ Fayetteville.